@em2machine commit 2736262b "Fix resolving default/nondefault type-of-type parameters (#7380) (#7385)"

on the following code which passed before this has three problems (presumably same bug):
1. It used to pass
2. Without --debug it will give different output from --debug, namely without debug an error about recursion, and with debug no error
3. With --debug it will hang in a loop involving AstRefDType::basicp.

The example uses UVM, for the "PR's test" please make a small version exhibiting the recursion without UVM.

Thanks

```
module t;
  import uvm_pkg::*;
  class c;
    int i;
    function bit compare(c rhs);
      return i == rhs.i;
    endfunction
    function void copy(c rhs);
      rhs.i = i;
    endfunction
  endclass
  initial begin
    uvm_in_order_class_comparator #(c) sb;
  end
endmodule
```

